TITLE: Contract and Transaction Information Access in EVM (Opcodes 0x30-0x37)
DESCRIPTION: Opcodes for accessing contract and transaction context information, including current contract address, account balances, transaction origin, message sender, value, and calldata. These provide essential information about the execution environment.

LANGUAGE: evm
CODE:
```
0x30 ADDRESS       // Stack input: .           Output: address(this)       // address of executing contract
0x31 BALANCE       // Stack input: addr        Output: addr.balance        // balance, in wei
0x32 ORIGIN        // Stack input: .           Output: tx.origin           // address that originated the tx
0x33 CALLER        // Stack input: .           Output: msg.sender          // address of msg sender
0x34 CALLVALUE     // Stack input: .           Output: msg.value           // msg value, in wei
0x35 CALLDATALOAD  // Stack input: idx         Output: msg.data[idx:idx+32] // read word from msg data at index idx
0x36 CALLDATASIZE  // Stack input: .           Output: len(msg.data)       // length of msg data, in bytes
0x37 CALLDATACOPY  // Stack input: dstOst, ost, len  Output: .  // mem[dstOst:dstOst+len-1] := msg.data[ost:ost+len-1]  // copy msg data
```

