TITLE: Querying Average Daily Block Count in Ethereum
DESCRIPTION: SQL query that calculates the average number of blocks produced per day on the Ethereum blockchain. The query first creates a temporary table grouping blocks by day, then calculates the overall average.

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
WITH temp_table AS (
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('day', time) AS dt,
    COUNT(*) AS block_count
FROM ethereum."blocks"
GROUP BY dt
OFFSET 1
)
SELECT
    AVG(block_count) AS avg_block_count
FROM temp_table
```

