TITLE: Main Function for Minesweeper Dig Verification in ZoKrates
DESCRIPTION: The main function for the dig program that generates zero-knowledge proofs for dig results. It takes a private map parameter and coordinates, returns the map hash and either 0xFF if a mine was hit or the count of surrounding mines.

LANGUAGE: zokrates
CODE:
```
def main(private bool[${width+2}][${height+2}] map, u32 x, u32 y) -> (field, u8) {
   return (hashMap(map),
         if map2mineCount(map, x, y) > 0 { 0xFF } else {
            map2mineCount(map, x-1, y-1) + map2mineCount(map, x, y-1) + map2mineCount(map, x+1, y-1) +
            map2mineCount(map, x-1, y) + map2mineCount(map, x+1, y) +
            map2mineCount(map, x-1, y+1) + map2mineCount(map, x, y+1) + map2mineCount(map, x+1, y+1)
         }
   );
}
```

