TITLE: Solidity Contract with Array Operations for Gas Testing
DESCRIPTION: A sample Solidity contract with array operations that can be used to demonstrate gas consumption patterns. It includes functions to push, pop, and clear an array, as well as a check function that loops through the array with nested loops.

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
contract C {
  address [] addrs;
  function push(address a) public {
    addrs.push(a);
  }
  function pop() public {
    addrs.pop();
  }
  function clear() public{
    addrs.length = 0;
  }
  function check() public{
    for(uint256 i = 0; i < addrs.length; i++)
      for(uint256 j = i+1; j < addrs.length; j++)
        if (addrs[i] == addrs[j])
