TITLE: Implementing Integer Encoding and Decoding for Dagger-Hashimoto in Python
DESCRIPTION: Functions for marshaling unsigned integers of 512-bit precision to strings using a big-endian scheme and vice versa. These are core utility functions used in the DAG generation process.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
NUM_BITS = 512

def encode_int(x):
    "Encode an integer x as a string of 64 characters using a big-endian scheme"
    o = ''
    for _ in range(NUM_BITS / 8):
        o = chr(x % 256) + o
        x //= 256
    return o

def decode_int(s):
    "Unencode an integer x from a string using a big-endian scheme"
    x = 0
    for c in s:
        x *= 256
        x += ord(c)
    return x
```

