TITLE: Analyzing Ethereum Block Production Metrics
DESCRIPTION: SQL query that calculates daily block production since 2016 and determines the average number of blocks produced per day, demonstrating Ethereum's consistency in block creation.

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
# query to visualize number of blocks produced daily since 2016

SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('day', time) AS dt,
    COUNT(*) AS block_count
FROM ethereum."blocks"
GROUP BY dt
OFFSET 1

# average number of blocks produced per day

WITH temp_table AS (
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('day', time) AS dt,
    COUNT(*) AS block_count
FROM ethereum."blocks"
GROUP BY dt
OFFSET 1
)
SELECT
    AVG(block_count) AS avg_block_count
FROM temp_table
```

