TITLE: Implementing Light-Client Block Verification in Python
DESCRIPTION: A light-client friendly version of the verification algorithm that doesn't require the full DAG. It uses quick_hashimoto to compute the result, enabling verification on devices with limited resources.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def light_verify(params, header, nonce):
    seedset = get_seedset(params, block)
    result = quick_hashimoto(seedset["front_hash"], get_dagsize(params, block),
                             params, decode_int(block.prevhash), nonce)
    return result * params["diff"] < 2**256
```

