TITLE: Light Client Evaluation Function for Dagger-Hashimoto
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a light client function to compute DAG values without storing the entire graph. It uses recursion and caching to efficiently calculate any node in the DAG by computing only a small subtree of nodes.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def quick_calc(params, seed, p):
    w, P = params["w"], params["P"]
    cache = {}

    def quick_calc_cached(p):
        if p in cache:
            pass
        elif p == 0:
            cache[p] = pow(sha3(seed), w, P)
        else:
            x = pow(sha3(seed), (p + 1) * w, P)
            for _ in range(params["k"]):
                x ^= quick_calc_cached(x % p)
            cache[p] = pow(x, w, P)
        return cache[p]

    return quick_calc_cached(p)
```

