TITLE: Implementing Light-Client Hashimoto Verification in Python
DESCRIPTION: A light-client friendly version of Hashimoto that doesn't require the full DAG. It uses a quick calculation function to generate DAG values on-the-fly, making verification possible without storing the entire dataset.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def quick_hashimoto(seed, dagsize, params, header, nonce):
    m = dagsize // 2
    mix = sha3(nonce + header)
    for _ in range(params["accesses"]):
        mix ^= quick_calc(params, seed, m + (mix % 2**64) % m)
    return dbl_sha3(mix)
```

