TITLE: Calculating Dataset Items in Ethash
DESCRIPTION: Function to compute a single 64-byte item in the Ethash dataset. Each item is derived by combining data from 256 pseudorandomly selected cache nodes and hashing the result.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def calc_dataset_item(cache, i):
    n = len(cache)
    r = HASH_BYTES // WORD_BYTES
    # initialize the mix
    mix = copy.copy(cache[i % n])
    mix[0] ^= i
    mix = sha3_512(mix)
    # fnv it with a lot of random cache nodes based on i
    for j in range(DATASET_PARENTS):
        cache_index = fnv(i ^ j, mix[j % r])
        mix = map(fnv, mix, cache[cache_index % n])
    return sha3_512(mix)
```

