TITLE: Implementing Modified Hashimoto for Dagger-Hashimoto in Python
DESCRIPTION: A modified version of Hashimoto that addresses the computational overhead issue by using only the least significant 64 bits when indexing the dataset. This implementation includes the full hashimoto function that operates on the DAG.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def hashimoto(dag, dagsize, params, header, nonce):
    m = dagsize / 2
    mix = sha3(encode_int(nonce) + header)
    for _ in range(params["accesses"]):
        mix ^= dag[m + (mix % 2**64) % m]
    return dbl_sha3(mix)
```

