TITLE: Calculating Cache and Dataset Sizes in Ethash
DESCRIPTION: Functions to determine the cache and dataset sizes for a given block number in the Ethash algorithm. The sizes grow linearly with epochs but are adjusted to the nearest prime to prevent cyclic behavior.

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def get_cache_size(block_number):
    sz = CACHE_BYTES_INIT + CACHE_BYTES_GROWTH * (block_number // EPOCH_LENGTH)
    sz -= HASH_BYTES
    while not isprime(sz / HASH_BYTES):
        sz -= 2 * HASH_BYTES
    return sz

def get_full_size(block_number):
    sz = DATASET_BYTES_INIT + DATASET_BYTES_GROWTH * (block_number // EPOCH_LENGTH)
    sz -= MIX_BYTES
    while not isprime(sz / MIX_BYTES):
        sz -= 2 * MIX_BYTES
    return sz
```

